14/05/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Defence Minister Vesselin Bliznakov announced on Saturday (May 12th) plans to boost the number of Bulgarian troops serving in the International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan by mid-June.
At NATO's request, Sofia will triple its current contribution of 80 troops, deployed in Kabul and Kandahar.
(bTV, BNT - 12/05/07)
